    <h1>MAP Minor League — Full Program Details</h1>

    <!-- OVERVIEW -->
    <details>
      <summary>Overview</summary>
      <div class="section-content">
        The MAP Minor League is the nation’s first dual-prep system for high school athletes, designed to prepare them for both college admissions and athletic recruiting. 
        This page provides a full breakdown of everything included in the core training program and in the optional Parent Pass™ add-on.
      </div>
    </details>

    <!-- TRAINING PROGRAM -->
    <details>
      <summary>What High School Athletes Receive (Tuition)</summary>
      <div class="section-content">

        <p class="subhead">8-Week Olympic Season</p>
        <p>Five weeks of academic training followed by three weeks of competition, mirroring the cadence of elite athletic development.</p>

        <p class="subhead">Weekly Film Study + Mentorship</p>
        <p>Live sessions led by MAP alumni across four breakout levels—Rookie, Single-A, Double-A, and Medal Round.</p>

        <p class="subhead">Academic Deliverables</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Résumé suitable for early college and scholarship applications</li>
          <li>College essay draft & narrative development</li>
          <li>Player Profile & Highlight Sheet</li>
          <li>Completed College-Ready Portfolio</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="subhead">Athletic & Recruiting Deliverables</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Film-development guidance</li>
          <li>Recruiting outreach templates</li>
          <li>Coach communication framework</li>
          <li>Recruiting progression roadmap</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="subhead">5 Rings of Dual Excellence</p>
        <p>Every athlete develops across five academic and athletic Rings: STEM, Business, Social Sciences, Arts & Communications, and Health & Medicine.</p>

      </div>
    </details>

    <!-- PARENT PASS -->
    <details>
      <summary>What Parents Receive with the Parent Pass™ (Add-On)</summary>
      <div class="section-content">

        <p class="subhead">Performance Intelligence Report™</p>
        <p>A 10–15 page professional-grade evaluation modeled after the tools used by firms recruiting MAP’s top college athletes.</p>

        <p class="subhead">MAP Benchmarking</p>
        <p>Data-driven comparisons to MAP alumni who have earned admission to elite universities and competitive athletic programs.</p>

        <p class="subhead">Competitive DNA & Leadership Profile</p>
        <p>Includes MAP Personality Type Code, Leadership Style, academic tendencies, and high-performance attributes.</p>

        <p class="subhead">Recruit-Ready Action Plan™</p>
        <p>A detailed 12-month roadmap outlining academic habits, athletic milestones, and recruiting steps to stay ahead.</p>

        <p class="subhead">Annual Re-Score Option</p>
        <p>Parents may update the evaluation each year to track progress through Rookie → Single-A → Double-A → Medal Round → MAP Major League.</p>

      </div>
    </details>

    <!-- PROGRESSION -->
    <details>
      <summary>Pathway Progression (Rookie → Medal Round → MAP Major League)</summary>
      <div class="section-content">

        <p class="subhead">9th Grade — Rookie League</p>
        <p>Fundamentals, identity discovery, early academic posture, and first portfolio-building exercises.</p>

        <p class="subhead">10th Grade — Single-A League</p>
        <p>Applying the Rings across mini-projects, first outreach to coaches, updated academic résumé.</p>

        <p class="subhead">11th Grade — Double-A League</p>
        <p>Case challenges, strategy integration, campus alignment, and essay development.</p>

        <p class="subhead">12th Grade — Medal Round</p>
        <p>Capstone specialization, mock interviews, final essay polishing, and admissions readiness.</p>

        <p class="subhead">College — MAP Major League</p>
        <p>Upon admission to university, athletes may enter MAP’s college-level professional development leagues.</p>

      </div>
    </details>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <details>
      <summary>Parent FAQs</summary>
      <div class="section-content">
        <p class="subhead">Do we need to play a varsity sport?</p>
        <p>No — the Minor League supports all competitive high school athletes, regardless of school team affiliation.</p>

        <p class="subhead">Can we purchase the Parent Pass™ without enrolling?</p>
        <p>Yes — many families use the evaluation and roadmap independently as they plan their child’s development.</p>

        <p class="subhead">Is financial aid available?</p>
        <p>MAP offers limited aid and scholarships based on need and potential impact.</p>

        <p class="subhead">How selective is the program?</p>
        <p>MAP evaluates interest, commitment, and development readiness holistically—not just athletic stats.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

